#TMSH-VERSION: 17.1.1.3

apm ephemeral-auth ssh-security-config /Common/ssh-security-config {
    ciphers {
        1 {
            cipher-name aes256-ctr
        }
        2 {
            cipher-name aes192-ctr
        }
        3 {
            cipher-name aes128-ctr
        }
    }
    compressions {
        1 {
            compression-name none
        }
    }
    hmacs {
        1 {
            hmac-name hmac-sha2-512
        }
        2 {
            hmac-name hmac-sha2-256
        }
    }
    kex-methods {
        1 {
            kex-method-name ecdh-sha2-nistp256
        }
    }
}
apm oauth db-instance /Common/oauthdb {
    description "Default OAuth DB."
}
apm policy access-policy /Common/kerberos_auth_config_default {
    default-ending /Common/kerberos_auth_config_default_end_deny
    items {
        /Common/kerberos_auth_config_default_act_kerberos_auth { }
        /Common/kerberos_auth_config_default_end_allow { }
        /Common/kerberos_auth_config_default_end_deny { }
        /Common/kerberos_auth_config_default_ent { }
    }
    start-item /Common/kerberos_auth_config_default_ent
}
apm policy customization-source /Common/modern { }
apm policy customization-source /Common/standard { }
apm policy policy-item /Common/kerberos_auth_config_default_act_kerberos_auth {
    agents {
        /Common/kerberos_auth_config_default_act_kerberos_auth_ag {
            type aaa-kerberos
        }
    }
    caption "Kerberos Auth"
    color 1
    item-type action
    rules {
        {
            caption Successful
            expression "expr {[mcget {session.kerberos.last.authresult}] == 1}"
            next-item /Common/kerberos_auth_config_default_end_allow
        }
        {
            caption fallback
            next-item /Common/kerberos_auth_config_default_end_deny
        }
    }
}
apm policy policy-item /Common/kerberos_auth_config_default_end_allow {
    agents {
        /Common/kerberos_auth_config_default_end_allow_ag {
            type ending-allow
        }
    }
    caption Allow
    color 1
    item-type ending
}
apm policy policy-item /Common/kerberos_auth_config_default_end_deny {
    agents {
        /Common/kerberos_auth_config_default_end_deny_ag {
            type ending-deny
        }
    }
    caption Deny
    color 2
    item-type ending
}
apm policy policy-item /Common/kerberos_auth_config_default_ent {
    caption Start
    color 1
    rules {
        {
            caption fallback
            next-item /Common/kerberos_auth_config_default_act_kerberos_auth
        }
    }
}
apm policy agent ending-allow /Common/kerberos_auth_config_default_end_allow_ag { }
apm policy agent ending-deny /Common/kerberos_auth_config_default_end_deny_ag {
    customization-group /Common/kerberos_auth_config_default_end_deny_ag
}
apm policy agent kerberos /Common/kerberos_auth_config_default_act_kerberos_auth_ag { }
apm report default-report {
    report-name sessionReports/sessionSummary
    user /Common/admin
}
auth ldap /Common/system-auth {
    bind-dn "CN=f5basedn,OU=Service Users,DC=RND,DC=COM"
    bind-pw **************************************************
    debug enabled
    idle-timeout 299
    login-attribute sAMAccountName
    referrals no
    search-base-dn DC=RND,DC=COM
    servers { 10.30.16.251 }
}
auth remote-role {
    role-info {
        /Common/F5_Admins {
            attribute "memberOF=CN=F5_Admins,OU=RND SGs,DC=RND,DC=COM"
            console tmsh
            line-order 1001
            role administrator
            user-partition All
        }
    }
}
auth source {
    fallback true
    type active-directory
}
ilx global-settings {
    debug-port-blacklist { 47019 54321 60000 }
}

ltm rule /Common/HTTP_2_HTTPS_partners {
when HTTP_REQUEST { 

		HTTP::redirect https://[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]
		#log local0. "[IP::client_addr] ========================"
		#log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri] redirect to HTTPS" 

}
}
ltm rule /Common/HTTP_2_HTTPS_temp {
when HTTP_REQUEST { 
    if { [IP::addr [IP::client_addr] equals 10.30.20.0%[ROUTE::domain]/24] }{ 
       #log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri] Allowed HTTP internally for subnet 20" }
    elseif { [IP::addr [IP::client_addr] equals 10.30.19.0%[ROUTE::domain]/24] }{ 
       #log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri] Allowed HTTP internally for subnet 19" }  
    elseif { [IP::addr [IP::client_addr] equals 10.30.21.0%[ROUTE::domain]/24] }{ 
       #log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri] Allowed HTTP internally for subnet 21" }
       else {
		HTTP::redirect https://[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]
		#log local0. "[IP::client_addr] ========================"
		#log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri] redirect to HTTPS" 
    }
}
}
ltm rule /Common/HTTP_TO_HTTPS_2 {
when HTTP_REQUEST {
    if { [IP::addr [IP::client_addr] equals 10.30.20.0%[ROUTE::domain]/24] }{ 
       #log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri] Allowed HTTP internally for subnet 20"
       } elseif { [IP::addr [IP::client_addr] equals 10.30.19.0%[ROUTE::domain]/24] }{ 
       #log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri] Allowed HTTP internally for subnet 20"
       } elseif { [IP::addr [IP::client_addr] equals 10.30.21.0%[ROUTE::domain]/24] }{ 
       #log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri] Allowed HTTP internally for subnet 21"
       } elseif { [IP::addr [IP::client_addr] equals 172.16.0.0%[ROUTE::domain]/24] }{ 
       #log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri] Allowed HTTP internally for subnet 16" 
       } elseif { [IP::addr [IP::client_addr] equals 10.92.0.0.0%[ROUTE::domain]/16] }{ 
       #log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri] Allowed HTTP internally for subnet 10.192" 
       } else {
       	#log local0. "[IP::client_addr] ========================"
		#log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri] redirect to HTTPS" 
		HTTP::redirect https://[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]
    }
}
}

ltm rule /Common/Not-Found-Error-Redirect {
when HTTP_REQUEST {
        set my_host_header [HTTP::host]
    }

    when HTTP_RESPONSE {
        if {[HTTP::status] eq "404"} {
            if { $my_host_header contains "qa.payoneer.com"}{
                HTTP::respond 302 Location "http://pubs.qa2.payoneer.com/Error/ErrorPage.html"
            }
            if { $my_host_header contains "firstchoicepay.com"}{
                HTTP::respond 302 Location "https://myaccount.sandbox.firstchoicepay.com/error/firstchoicepay/ErrorPage.html?err=404-20161228-79818"
            }
        }
    }
}

ltm rule /Common/QA2_apicert_error {
when HTTP_REQUEST {

set uri [string tolower [HTTP::uri]]
if { $uri contains "apicert_error" } {
        set response {
           <?xml version='1.0' encoding='ISO-8859-1' ?>
                <PayoneerResponse>
                    <Status>A00B556F</Status>
                    <Description>Rule Unauthorized Access or invalid parameters, please check your IP address and parameters.</Description>
                </PayoneerResponse>
                }
    HTTP::respond 500 content $response noserver "Content-Type" "text/html; charset=utf-8"
    }
}
}
ltm rule /Common/QA2_apicert_rule {
when CLIENT_ACCEPTED {
    set invalidate_session 0
    set ssl_errstr 0
    #log local0. $invalidate_session
}

#when CLIENTSSL_HANDSHAKE {
#    set ssl_stuff [list anything1 anything2]
#    set ssl_cert [SSL::cert 0]
#    set ssl_errstr [X509::verify_cert_error_string [SSL::verify_result]]
#    lset ssl_stuff 0 $ssl_cert
#    lset ssl_stuff 1 $ssl_errstr
    #session add ssl [SSL::sessionid] $ssl_stuff 180
#}

when CLIENTSSL_CLIENTCERT {
  set invalidate_session 0
  set ssl_stuff [list anything1 anything2]
  set ssl_cert [SSL::cert 0]
  set ssl_errstr [X509::verify_cert_error_string [SSL::verify_result]]
  lset ssl_stuff 0 $ssl_cert
  lset ssl_stuff 1 $ssl_errstr
  if { [SSL::cert count] < 1 } {
    set invalidate_session 1
  }
  if { $ssl_errstr eq "ok" } {
    set invalidate_session 0
  }
  else {
    set invalidate_session 1
  }
  session add ssl [SSL::sessionid] $ssl_stuff 180
  #set sid [SSL::sessionid]
}

when HTTP_REQUEST {
###### set headerlog to 0 to disable header logging ######
  set headerlog 1
  set check1 1
  set ssl_stuff2 [session lookup ssl [SSL::sessionid]]
  set ssl_cert2 [lindex $ssl_stuff2 0]
  set ssl_errstr2 [lindex $ssl_stuff2 1]
  if { $invalidate_session eq 0} {             
        HTTP::header insert CCRT-SN [X509::serial_number $ssl_cert2]
        HTTP::header insert X-Forwarded-Host [HTTP::host]
        #HTTP::header insert X-Forwarded-Proto
        log local0. [HTTP::header Connection]
        HTTP::header replace "Connection" "Close"
        log local0. [HTTP::header Connection]
        }
  elseif {$invalidate_session}{
		if { [string tolower [HTTP::uri]] contains "/v2/" } {
            set response {
             {
                    "audit_id": 0,
                    "code": 10000,
                    "description": "Invalid Certificate",
                    "hint": "please contact Integration Support"
            }
		}
            #log local0. $response
            #log local0. "IP - [IP::client_addr] Cert count - [SSL::cert count] - error - $ssl_errstr"
            HTTP::respond 500 content $response noserver "Content-Type" "application/json; charset=utf-8"
            }
else {
set response {
			<?xml version='1.0' encoding='ISO-8859-1' ?>
			<PayoneerResponse>
				<Status>A00B556F</Status>
				<Description>Unauthorized Access or invalid parameters, please check your IP address and parameters.</Description>
			</PayoneerResponse>
		}
		#log local0. $response
		#log local0. "IP - [IP::client_addr] Cert count - [SSL::cert count] - error - $ssl_errstr"
		HTTP::respond 500 content $response noserver "Content-Type" "text/html; charset=utf-8"
}
		session delete ssl [SSL::sessionid]
		SSL::session invalidate
		TCP::close
  }



    if { $headerlog eq 1 && $invalidate_session eq 0} { 
        foreach hdr [HTTP::header names] {
             log local0. "HTTP Header : $hdr = [HTTP::header values $hdr]"
        }
        log local0. "IP - [IP::client_addr] Cert count - [SSL::cert count] - error - $ssl_errstr"
    }
}
}
ltm rule /Common/QA2_apiclientcert_rule {
when RULE_INIT {
  set ::debug 1
}

when CLIENT_ACCEPTED {
  if { [IP::addr [IP::client_addr]/16 equals 192.168.0.0%[ROUTE::domain]] or [IP::addr [IP::client_addr]/24 equals 10.200.2.0%[ROUTE::domain]] }{
    set office 1
    SSL::profile payoneer_qa_ssl_noIrule_clientcert
    if { $::debug }{ log local0. "APICERT: Client from office" }
  } else {
    set office 0
    if { $::debug }{ log local0. "APICERT: Client not from office" }
  }
}

when CLIENTSSL_CLIENTCERT {
  set ssl_cert [SSL::cert 0]
}

when HTTP_REQUEST {
  if { $::debug } {
    log local0. "APICERT: [HTTP::header Host]"
  }

  HTTP::header replace "Host" "apicert.qa2.payoneer.com"
  #HTTP::header replace "Connection" "Close"

  if { $office eq 1 } {
    HTTP::header insert CCRT-SN [X509::serial_number $ssl_cert]
    HTTP::header insert X-Forwarded-Host [HTTP::host]
    if { $::debug } {
      log local0. "APICERT: IP - [IP::client_addr] Cert count - [SSL::cert count]"
    }
  }

  if { $::debug } {
    foreach hdr [HTTP::header names] {
      log local0. "APICERT: HTTP Header : $hdr = [HTTP::header values $hdr]"
    }
  }
}
}
ltm rule /Common/QA2_apiecert_rewrite {
when CLIENTSSL_HANDSHAKE {
  set cur [SSL::sessionid]
  set ask [session lookup ssl $cur] 
  if { $ask eq "" } { 
    session add ssl [SSL::sessionid] [SSL::cert 0]
  }
}

when HTTP_REQUEST {
  set id [SSL::sessionid]
  set the_cert [session lookup ssl $id]
  if { $the_cert != ""}
  {
    HTTP::header remove x-client-cert
    HTTP::header remove ccrt-sn
    binary scan [sha1 $the_cert] H* fingerprint
    HTTP::header insert x-client-cert $fingerprint
    HTTP::header insert ccrt-sn [string map -nocase [list ":" ""] [X509::serial_number $the_cert]]
  }
  HTTP::uri "/payoneer/qa/apie[HTTP::uri]"
}
}

ltm rule /Common/QA2_apigee_webbo {
when HTTP_REQUEST {
  set rewrite_trigger [string tolower [HTTP::uri]]
  switch -regexp $rewrite_trigger {
    "^/gw-" {
      persist none
            HTTP::header insert "x-forwarded-host" [HTTP::host]
            HTTP::header replace "Host" "apigwebbo.qa2.payoneer.com"
            virtual QA2_apigeegw_https
        }
    }   
}
}
ltm rule /Common/QA2_app_redirect {
when HTTP_REQUEST {
	set hostname [string tolower [HTTP::host]]
	set uri [string tolower [HTTP::uri]]
	set path [string tolower [HTTP::path]]
	set rewrite_trigger [string tolower [HTTP::uri]]
 	switch -regexp $rewrite_trigger {
    "^/gw-" {
		#set rewrite_trigger [string tolower [HTTP::uri]]
		SSL::enable serverside
    	HTTP::header insert "x-forwarded-host" [HTTP::host]
		HTTP::header replace "Host" "apiginternal.qa2.payoneer.com"
		virtual QA2_apigeegw_https
	}
	"^/favicon" {
	    SSL::disable serverside
		pool QA2_pubs_80
		HTTP::header replace "Host" "pubs.qa2.payoneer.com"
		if { [HTTP::path] equals "/favicon.ico" }{
		    #log local0. "/Content/Default/img/Favicon/favicon.ico"
        	HTTP::uri "/Content/Default/img/Favicon/favicon.ico"
        }
        elseif {[HTTP::path] equals "/favicon-16x16.png" }{
            #log local0. "/Content/Default/img/Favicon/favicon-16x16.png"
		    HTTP::uri "/Content/Default/img/Favicon/favicon-16x16.png"
        }
        elseif { [HTTP::path] equals "/favicon-32x32.png"  }{
            #log local0. "/Content/Default/img/Favicon/favicon-32x32.png"
          	HTTP::uri "/Content/Default/img/Favicon/favicon-32x32.png"
        }
        else {
			#OOOPPSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSS page
			HTTP::respond 302 Location "https://www.payoneer.com/404/"		    
        }

	}
    "^/apple-touch-icon" {
	    SSL::disable serverside
		pool QA2_pubs_80
		HTTP::header replace "Host" "pubs.qa2.payoneer.com"
		if { [HTTP::path] equals "/apple-touch-icon-152x152.png" }{
		    #log local0. "/Content/Default/img/Favicon/apple-touch-icon-152x152.png"
        	HTTP::uri "/Content/Default/img/Favicon/apple-touch-icon-152x152.png"
		}
        else {
			#OOOPPSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSS page
			HTTP::respond 302 Location "https://www.payoneer.com/404/"		    
        }
	}
	default {
		log local0. "my path: $path"
	    if {not(($path ends_with "/")) && [class match "$path/" equals QA2_app_dg]} {
	        HTTP::path $path/
	        set flag 0
		}
		elseif { [class match $path starts_with QA2_app_dg] } { #regular slash in the end
		    set flag 1
        } 
        else {
            set flag 2
			#OOOPPSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSS page
			HTTP::respond 302 Location "https://www.payoneer.com/404/"
		}

		if {$flag < 2} {
		    SSL::disable serverside
    		set parameters_DG [class match -value [HTTP::path] starts_with QA2_app_dg]
    		set SLIT_POINT [getfield $parameters_DG # 2 ]
    		HTTP::uri [string range [HTTP::path] $SLIT_POINT end]
            set NEW_HOST [getfield $parameters_DG # 1 ]
    		set TO_POOL [getfield $parameters_DG # 3 ]
    		HTTP::header replace "Host" $NEW_HOST
    		pool $TO_POOL
    		log local0. "$NEW_HOST[HTTP::uri]"


		}
	}

}
}
}
ltm rule /Common/QA2_auth_rewrite {
when CLIENT_ACCEPTED {
SSL::disable serverside
}

when HTTP_REQUEST {
  if { [HTTP::uri] starts_with "/gw-auth"} {
    SSL::enable serverside
    # Check for apigee mfa header
    if { [HTTP::header "X-Payoneer-MFA-Version"] equals "a" } {
      HTTP::header insert "x-forwarded-host" [HTTP::host]
      HTTP::header replace "Host" "apiginternal.qa2.payoneer.com"
      virtual QA2_apigeegw_https
    } else {
      HTTP::header replace "Host" "api.qa2.payoneer.openapi.qa2.payoneer.com"
      HTTP::uri "[HTTP::uri]"
      #log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
      pool "QA2_openapi_443"
    }
  } else {
    pool "QA2_auth_80"
    #log local0. "if was not applied"
  }
}
}
ltm rule /Common/QA2_azuregw_rewrite {
when CLIENT_ACCEPTED {
    #log local0. "azuregw tcp started"
}
when HTTP_REQUEST {
    # local0. "[HTTP::host]"
    # local0. "azuregw started"
    if {([HTTP::host] eq "azuregw.qa2.payoneer.com") and ([HTTP::uri] starts_with "/azure")} {
        #log local0. "correct host header "
        HTTP::header insert "x-forwarded-host" [HTTP::host]
        HTTP::header replace "Host" "apigazure.qa2.payoneer.com"
        #log local0. "[HTTP::uri]"
        HTTP::uri [string map {"/azure/" "/"} [HTTP::uri]]
        #log local0. "[HTTP::uri]"
        #log local0. "good"
        virtual QA2_apigeegw_https 
    } else {
        HTTP::respond 302 Location "https://www.payoneer.com/oops/"
        #log local0. "302"
    }
}
}
ltm rule /Common/QA2_casemgmtgw_rewrite {
when CLIENT_ACCEPTED {
    #log local0. "appian tcp started"
}
when HTTP_REQUEST {
    # local0. "[HTTP::host]"
    # local0. "case started"
    if {[HTTP::host] eq "casemgmtgw.qa2.payoneer.com" } {
        #log local0. "correct host header "
        HTTP::header insert "x-forwarded-host" [HTTP::host]
        HTTP::header replace "Host" "apigcasemgmt.qa2.payoneer.com"
        #log local0. "[HTTP::uri]"
        HTTP::uri "/casemgmt[HTTP::uri]"
        #log local0. "[HTTP::uri]"
        #log local0. "good"
        virtual QA2_apigeegw_https 
    } else {
        HTTP::respond 302 Location "https://www.payoneer.com/oops/"
        #log local0. "302"
    }
}
}
ltm rule /Common/QA2_developer_rewrite {
when HTTP_REQUEST {
if { [HTTP::host] equals "developer.dev.payoneer.com" } {
        HTTP::redirect "https://developer.qa2.payoneer.com/payoneer/dev/"
        #log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
    } elseif { [HTTP::uri] equals "/" } {
        HTTP::redirect "https://developer.qa2.payoneer.com/payoneer/qa/"
        #log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
    }
}
}
ltm rule /Common/QA2_direct_pools {
when CLIENT_ACCEPTED {
   set member_debug 0
   if { [IP::addr [IP::client_addr]/16 equals 192.168.0.0%[ROUTE::domain]] } {
      set office 1
      if {$member_debug} { log local0. "Client from office" }
   } elseif { [IP::addr [IP::client_addr]/24 equals 10.200.2.0%[ROUTE::domain]] } {
      set office 1
      if {$member_debug} { log local0. "Client from office" }
   } else {
      set office 0
      if {$member_debug} { log local0. "Client not from office" }
   }

}

when HTTP_REQUEST {
   # set office 1
   set member_lb [LB::server pool]
   if {$office} {

      # Log debug to /var/log/ltm? 1=yes, 0=no. Both should be set to 1
      set member_debug 0
      set webbo_logs 1

      # Set to 1 to active logs in webbo also and unremark
      #if { [HTTP::host] contains "webbo"} {  set webbo_logs 0 }

      # Name of the URI parameter name used to manually select a specific pool member
      # Clients can append the member parameter to a query string in the format of:
      #   www.example.com/index.html?member=2
      # where member is the parameter name
      set member_param "member"

      # Track whether a member has been found in the query string or cookie
      set member_num ""
      if { [HTTP::cookie member_lb] ne ""} {
         pool [HTTP::cookie member_lb]
         set member_lb [HTTP::cookie member_lb]
      }

      # Debug logging
      if { $member_debug and $webbo_logs} {
         log local0. "[LB::server pool]"
         log local0. "[IP::client_addr]:[TCP::client_port]: Debug enabled on [HTTP::method] request for [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
         log local0. "[IP::client_addr]:[TCP::client_port]: Members for pool [LB::server pool] (sorted):\
            [lsort [members -list [LB::server pool]]]"
      }

      # Check if query string contains "member=" before evaluating the value
      # Could replace this with a check of the URI that is only used when
      #   manually selecting a specific pool member.
      # Also check for a previously set cookie indicating a manually selected pool member.
      if {[HTTP::query] contains $member_param or [HTTP::cookie $member_param] ne ""} {
         # Have the query string parameter take precedence over the cookie.
         # So set the member_num based on the cookie and then overwrite it if the param value is set.
         set member_num [HTTP::cookie $member_param]
         if { $member_debug and $webbo_logs} { log local0. "[IP::client_addr]:[TCP::client_port]: Query contained the member parameter or member cookie was present.\
            Parsed member cookie value: $member_num" }

         set query_member_num [URI::query "?&[HTTP::query]" "&${member_param}"]
         if {$query_member_num ne ""} {
            set member_num $query_member_num
            if { $member_debug and $webbo_logs } { log local0. "[IP::client_addr]:[TCP::client_port]: Using member number from URI: \$member_num: $member_num" }
         }

         # Check member number value
         switch -glob $member_num {
            "0" {
               # Exact match for 0 (client wants to clear cookie)
               # Delete the cookie in the response

               # Save the cookie value so we can delete it in the response
               set cookie_val [HTTP::cookie $member_param]

               if {$member_debug and $webbo_logs} { log local0. "[IP::client_addr]:[TCP::client_port]: Member 0 specified, will remove cookie in response." }
               return
            }
            "[0-9]*" {
               # The parameter had a value starting with a digit,
               # Use lindex to get the nth -1 pool member "IP port" (lindex is 0 based)
               # Use scan to parse the IP and port to separate variables (the pool command doesn't seem to handle them together)
               # Use catch to handle any errors trying to parse the pool member
               if {[catch {scan [lindex [lsort [members -list [LB::server pool]]] [expr {$member_num - 1}]] {%[^ ] %d} ip port} result]} {

                  if { $member_debug and $webbo_logs } { log local0. "[IP::client_addr]:[TCP::client_port]: Error parsing pool member from $member_num" }

               } elseif {$result == 2} {

                  if { $member_debug and $webbo_logs } { log local0. "[IP::client_addr]:[TCP::client_port]: Parsed IP port: $ip $port" }

                  # Use catch to handle any errors trying to select the pool member
                  if {not [catch {node $ip $port}]} {
                     log local0. "URI is [HTTP::uri]"
                     log local0. "path is [HTTP::path]"
                     if {[URI::query [HTTP::uri]] contains $member_param} {
                        set newq ""
                        foreach param [split [URI::query [HTTP::uri]] "&"] {
                           if {!($param starts_with $member_param)} {
                              # Build up new query parameter string
                              if { $newq eq "" } {
                                 append newq "?$param"
                              } else {
                                 append newq "&$param"
                              }
                           }
                           # Add new query portion to path
                           HTTP::uri "[HTTP::path]$newq"
                        }
                     }
                     log local0. "URI is [HTTP::uri]"
                     log local0. "path is [HTTP::path]"
                     # Selecting pool member succeeded so exit this event of this iRule
                     if { $member_debug and $webbo_logs } { log local0. "[IP::client_addr]:[TCP::client_port]: Successfully selected: $ip $port" }
                     return
                  }
               }
            }
         }
         # If we're still in the iRule there was no match or there were errors trying to select the pool member
         # so load balance the request
         node [IP::client_addr]:[TCP::client_port]
         unset member_num --
         if { $member_debug and $webbo_logs } { log local0. "[IP::client_addr]:[TCP::client_port]: No/invalid member_num parsed, load balancing request" }
      }
   }
}

when HTTP_RESPONSE {

   # Check if $member_num is set and has a value
   if {[info exists member_num] and $member_num ne ""} {

      switch $member_num {
         0 {
            if {$cookie_val ne ""} {
               # Expire the cookie by inserting the name/value with an expire time in the past
               if { $member_debug and $webbo_logs } { log local0. "[IP::client_addr]:[TCP::client_port]: Expiring cookie $member_param=$cookie_val" }
               HTTP::cookie insert name $member_param value $cookie_val path "/"
               HTTP::cookie expires $member_param 0 absolute
               HTTP::cookie expires member_lb 0 absolute
            }
         }
         default {
            if { $member_debug and $webbo_logs} {log local0. "[IP::client_addr]:[TCP::client_port]: Inserting cookie $member_param=$member_num"}
            HTTP::cookie insert name $member_param value $member_num path "/"
            if {$member_debug and $webbo_logs} {log local0. "[IP::client_addr]:[TCP::client_port]: Inserting cookie member_lb=$member_lb"}
            HTTP::cookie insert name member_lb value $member_lb path "/"
         }
      }
   }
}
# Debug events which can be removed once testing is complete
when LB_SELECTED {
   if {$member_debug and $webbo_logs} { log local0. "[IP::client_addr]:[TCP::client_port]: Selected IP:port: [LB::server]" }
}
when SERVER_CONNECTED {
   if {$member_debug and $webbo_logs} { log local0. "[IP::client_addr]:[TCP::client_port]: Server IP:port: [IP::server_addr]:[TCP::server_port]" }
}
}
ltm rule /Common/QA2_emailsenderservice_rewrite {
when HTTP_REQUEST {
HTTP::header replace "port" "55858"
#log local0. "redirected to [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
}
}
ltm rule /Common/QA2_hackathon_rewrites {
when HTTP_REQUEST {
#### Set Parameters
    set hostname [string tolower [HTTP::host]]
    set uri [string tolower [HTTP::uri]]
    set uri_start [substr [HTTP::uri] 1 "/"]
    set NEW_HOST "$uri_start.qa2.payoneer.com"
    set SLIT_POINT {expr 1 + [string length [substr [HTTP::uri] 1 "/"]]};

#### Print parameters


#### Set host and uri
    log local0. $hostname
    if { $uri starts_with "/hack"} {
        HTTP::header replace "Host" $NEW_HOST
        log local0. $NEW_HOST
        log local0. $SLIT_POINT
        log local0. $uri
        set uri2 [string range [HTTP::uri] $SLIT_POINT end]
        log local0. "uri2: $uri2"
        HTTP::uri $uri2                
#### Print final URL
        log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
        pool "QA2_hackathon_80"
    }
}
when HTTP_RESPONSE { 
    if { ([HTTP::status] == "301") || ([HTTP::status] == "302") } {
        log local0. "[HTTP::header Location]"
    }    
}
}
ltm rule /Common/QA2_ipcncert_rule {
when CLIENT_ACCEPTED {
    set invalidate_session 1
    log local0. $invalidate_session
}

when CLIENTSSL_CLIENTCERT {
  set invalidate_session 0
  set ssl_stuff [list anything1 anything2]
  set ssl_cert [SSL::cert 0]
  set ssl_errstr [X509::verify_cert_error_string [SSL::verify_result]]
  lset ssl_stuff 0 $ssl_cert
  lset ssl_stuff 1 $ssl_errstr
  if { [SSL::cert count] < 1 } {
    set invalidate_session 1
  }
  if { $ssl_errstr eq "ok" } {
    set invalidate_session 0
  }
  else {
    set invalidate_session 1
  }
  session add ssl [SSL::sessionid] $ssl_stuff 180
}

when HTTP_REQUEST {
  ###### set headerlog to 0 to disable header logging ######
  set headerlog 1
  set check1 1
  set ssl_stuff2 [session lookup ssl [SSL::sessionid]]
  set ssl_cert2 [lindex $ssl_stuff2 0]
  set ssl_errstr2 [lindex $ssl_stuff2 1]
  if { $invalidate_session eq 0} {
    HTTP::header insert CCRT-SN [X509::serial_number $ssl_cert2]
    HTTP::header insert X-Forwarded-Host [HTTP::host]
    HTTP::header insert CCRT-Version [X509::version $ssl_cert2]
    HTTP::header insert CCRT-SignatureAlgo [X509::signature_algorithm $ssl_cert2]
    HTTP::header insert CCRT-Issuer [X509::issuer $ssl_cert2]
    HTTP::header insert CCRT-NotBefore [X509::not_valid_before $ssl_cert2]
    HTTP::header insert CCRT-NotAfter [X509::not_valid_after $ssl_cert2]
    HTTP::header insert CCRT-Subject [X509::subject $ssl_cert2]
    HTTP::header insert CCRT-PublicKeyType [X509::subject_public_key_type $ssl_cert2]
    HTTP::header insert CCRT-Certificate [X509::whole $ssl_cert2]
    HTTP::header insert CCRT-MD5Hash [X509::hash $ssl_cert2]
    #HTTP::header insert X-Forwarded-Proto
  }
  elseif {$invalidate_session}{
    if { [string tolower [HTTP::uri]] contains "/v2/" } {
      set response {
        {
          "audit_id": 0,
          "code": 10000,
          "description": "Invalid Certificate",
          "hint": "please contact Integration Support"
        }
      }
      #log local0. $response
      HTTP::respond 500 content $response noserver "Content-Type" "application/json; charset=utf-8"
    }
    else {
      set response {
        <?xml version='1.0' encoding='ISO-8859-1' ?>
        <PayoneerResponse>
        <Status>A00B556F</Status>
        <Description>Unauthorized Access or invalid parameters, please check your IP address and parameters.</Description>
        </PayoneerResponse>
      }
      log local0. $response
      HTTP::respond 500 content $response noserver "Content-Type" "text/html; charset=utf-8"
    }
    session delete ssl [SSL::sessionid]
    SSL::session invalidate
    TCP::close
  }



  if { $headerlog eq 1} {
    foreach hdr [HTTP::header names] {
      log local0. "HTTP Header : $hdr = [HTTP::header values $hdr]"
    }
  }
}
when SERVER_CLOSED {
  log local0. "Server [IP::server_addr] has closed the connection"
  set invalidate_session 1
    }
}
ltm rule /Common/QA2_lbserver {
when HTTP_REQUEST {
 log local0. "[LB::server]" 


 foreach hdr [HTTP::header names] {
             log local0. "HTTP Header : $hdr = [HTTP::header values $hdr]"
        }
}
}
ltm rule /Common/QA2_login_cn_mfa {
when HTTP_REQUEST { 
    set rewrite_trigger [string tolower [HTTP::uri]]
	    switch -regexp $rewrite_trigger {
				  "^/api/" {
					    HTTP::header replace "Host" "loginapi.qa2.payoneer.com.cn"
				        #log local0. "1. [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
					    pool "QA2_loginapi_cn_80"
					    }
				 "^/gw-auth" {
                        HTTP::header replace "Host" "api.qa2.payoneer.openapi.qa2.payoneer.com"
				        pool "QA2_openapi_80"
				        #log local0. "2. [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
		                }
                  "^/auth" {
					    HTTP::header replace "Host" "auth.qa2.payoneer.com.cn"
					    #log local0. "3. [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
					    pool "QA2_auth_cn_80"
					    }
				  default {
					    pool "QA2_login_cn_80"
					    #log local0. "4. [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
					    }
                    }
                }
}
ltm rule /Common/QA2_login_mfa {
when HTTP_REQUEST { 
    set rewrite_trigger [string tolower [HTTP::uri]]
	    switch -regexp $rewrite_trigger {
				  "^/api/" {
					    HTTP::header replace "Host" "loginapi.qa2.payoneer.com"
				        #log local0. "1. [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
					    pool "QA2_loginapi_80"
					    }
				 "^/gw-auth" {

                            HTTP::header insert "x-forwarded-host" [HTTP::host]
                            HTTP::header replace "Host" "apiginternal.qa2.payoneer.com"
                            log local0. "APIGEE: Got x-header will redirect to apiginternal"
                            #virtual QA2_apigeegw_https
                            pool QA2_apigeegw_9098
		                }
		         "^/auth" {
					    HTTP::header replace "Host" "auth.qa2.payoneer.com"
					    #log local0. "3. [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
					    pool "QA2_auth_80"
					    }
				  default {
					    pool "QA2_login_80"
					    #log local0. "4. [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
					    }
                    }
                }
}

  }
}

ltm rule /Common/QA2_ma_rewrite {
when HTTP_REQUEST { 
    set rewrite_trigger [string tolower [HTTP::uri]]
    #log local0. "0. [LB::server addr] [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
	    switch -regexp $rewrite_trigger {
	    		 "^/ma/" {
					HTTP::header replace "Host" "ma.qa2.payoneer.com"
					set uri2 [string range [HTTP::uri] 3 end]
					HTTP::uri $uri2
					pool "QA2_ma_80"
					#log local0. "1. [LB::server addr] [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
					}

					"^/ma-" {
					set uri1 [HTTP::uri]
					set maid [substr $uri1 1 "/"]
                    HTTP::header replace "Host" $maid.qa2.payoneer.com
				    HTTP::uri [string map -nocase "/$maid/ /" [HTTP::uri]]
				    pool "QA2_mafeaturerelease_80"
				    log local0. "[LB::server]" 
				    log local0. "4. [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
					}

					"^/login/" {
					HTTP::header replace "Host" "login.qa2.payoneer.com"
					set uri2 [string range [HTTP::uri] 6 end]
					HTTP::uri $uri2
					pool "QA2_login_80"
					#log local0. "1. [LB::server addr] [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
					}

					"^/login-" {
					set uri1 [HTTP::uri]
					set loginid [substr $uri1 1 "/"]
                    HTTP::header replace "Host" $loginid.qa2.payoneer.com
				    HTTP::uri [string map -nocase "/$loginid/ /" [HTTP::uri]]
				    pool "QA2_login_80"
				    log local0. "[LB::server]" 
				    log local0. "4. [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
					}

					"^/auth/" {
					HTTP::header replace "Host" "auth.qa2.payoneer.com"
					set uri2 [string range [HTTP::uri] 5 end]
					HTTP::uri $uri2
					pool "QA2_auth_80"
					#log local0. "1. [LB::server addr] [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
					}

			default {
					pool "QA2_pubs_80"
#					log local0. "3. [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
					}

	    }

}
}

ltm rule /Common/QA2_myaccount_cn_rewrites {
when HTTP_REQUEST { 
    set rewrite_trigger [string tolower [HTTP::uri]]
	    switch -regexp $rewrite_trigger {
			"^/gw-" {
				    HTTP::header replace "Host" "api.qa2.payoneer.openapi.qa2.payoneer.com"
				    pool "QA2_openapi_80"
				    #log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
			        }
		   "^/prqs" {
					HTTP::header replace "Host" "prqservice.qa2.payoneer.com"
					HTTP::uri [string map {"/prqs/" "/"} [HTTP::uri]]
					pool "QA2_prqservice_80"
					#log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
					}
		 "^/prqapi" {
					HTTP::header replace "Host" "paymentrequestapi.qa2.payoneer.com"
					HTTP::uri [string map {"/prqapi/" "/"} [HTTP::uri]]
					pool "QA2_paymentrequestapi_80"
					#log local0. "1. [LB::server addr] [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
					}
		 "^/brsapi" {
					HTTP::header replace "Host" "billingreportservice.qa2.payoneer.com"
					HTTP::uri [string map {"/brsapi/" "/"} [HTTP::uri]]
					pool "QA2_billingreportservice_80"
					#log local0. "2. [LB::server addr] [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
					}
         "^/payer" {
					HTTP::header replace "Host" "ma.qa2.payoneer.com"
					#HTTP::uri [string map {"/payer/" "/"} [HTTP::uri]]
					#log local0. "4. [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
					pool "QA2_ma_80"
					}
        "^/ma(/|$)" {
					HTTP::header replace "Host" "ma.qa2.payoneer.com.cn"
					if {[HTTP::uri] contains "."} {
					HTTP::uri [string map {"/ma/" "/"} [HTTP::uri]]
					}
				    else {
				    HTTP::uri "/index.ma.html"
				    }
					pool "QA2_ma_cn_80"
					#log local0. "6. [LB::server addr] [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
					}
			default {
					pool "QA2_myaccount_cn_80"
					#log local0. "5. [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
					}

	    }

}
}
ltm rule /Common/QA2_myaccount_lostpwd_2_login_forgotpwd {
when HTTP_REQUEST {
	if { [string tolower [HTTP::host]] equals "myaccount.qa2.firstchoicepay.com" and [string tolower [HTTP::uri]] starts_with "/login/lostpassword.aspx" } {
		HTTP::redirect "http://login.qa2.firstchoicepay.com/forgotpassword"
	}
    if { [string tolower [HTTP::host]] equals "myaccount.qa2.payoneer.com" and [string tolower [HTTP::uri]] starts_with "/login/lostpassword.aspx" } {
		HTTP::redirect "http://login.qa2.payoneer.com/forgotpassword"
	}
}
}
ltm rule /Common/QA2_myaccount_rewrites {
when HTTP_REQUEST {
  set rewrite_trigger [string tolower [HTTP::uri]]
  switch -regexp $rewrite_trigger {
    "^/gw-" {
      persist none
        #log local0. "APIGEE: [HTTP::header value Authorization]"
        HTTP::header insert "x-forwarded-host" [HTTP::host]
        HTTP::header replace "Host" "apiginternal.qa2.payoneer.com"
        #log local0. "APIGEE - [HTTP::uri]"
        #virtual QA2_apigeegw_https
        pool QA2_apigeegw_9098
    }
    "^/ma-" {
					set uri1 [HTTP::uri]
					set maid [substr $uri1 1 "/"]
                    HTTP::header replace "Host" $maid.qa2.payoneer.com
				    HTTP::uri [string map -nocase "/$maid/ /" [HTTP::uri]]
				    pool "QA2_mafeaturerelease_80"
				    #log local0. "[LB::server]" 
				    #log local0. "4. [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
					}
    "^/prqs" {
      HTTP::header replace "Host" "prqservice.qa2.payoneer.com"
      HTTP::uri [string map {"/prqs/" "/"} [HTTP::uri]]
      pool "QA2_prqservice_80"
      #log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
    }
    "^/brsapi" {
      HTTP::header replace "Host" "billingreportservice.qa2.payoneer.com"
      HTTP::uri [string map {"/brsapi/" "/"} [HTTP::uri]]
      pool "QA2_billingreportservice_80"
      #log local0. "2. [LB::server addr] [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
    }
    "^/auth/" {
      HTTP::header replace "Host" "auth.qa2.payoneer.com"
      HTTP::uri [string map {"/auth/" "/"} [HTTP::uri]]
      pool "QA2_auth_80"
      #log local0. "2. [LB::server addr] [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
    }
     "^/setupmyaccount" {
      HTTP::header replace "Host" "setupmyaccount.qa2.payoneer.com"
      HTTP::uri [string map {"/setupmyaccount/" "/"} [HTTP::uri]]
      pool "QA2_setupmyaccount_80"
      #log local0. "2. [LB::server addr] [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
    }
    "^/payer" {
      HTTP::header replace "Host" "ma.qa2.payoneer.com"
      #HTTP::uri [string map {"/payer/" "/"} [HTTP::uri]]
      #log local0. "4. [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
      pool "QA2_ma_80"
    }
    "^/methodregistration" {
      HTTP::header replace "Host" "methodregistration.qa2.payoneer.com"
      HTTP::uri [string map {"/methodregistration/" "/"} [HTTP::uri]]
      log local0. "methodregistration. [LB::server addr] [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
      pool "QA2_methodregistration_80"
    }
    "^/ma(/|$)" {
      HTTP::header replace "Host" "ma.qa2.payoneer.com"
      if {[HTTP::uri] contains "."} {
        HTTP::uri [string map {"/ma/" "/"} [HTTP::uri]]
      }
      else {
        HTTP::uri "/index.ma.html"
      }
      pool "QA2_ma_80"
      #log local0. "6. [LB::server addr] [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
    }
    default {
      pool "QA2_myaccount_80"
      #log local0. "5. [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
    }

  }

}
}

when HTTP_REQUEST {

					HTTP::uri [string map {"/auth/" "/"} [HTTP::uri]]
					pool "QA2_auth_80"
					#log local0. "2. [LB::server addr] [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
					}

         "^/payer" {
					HTTP::header replace "Host" "ma.qa2.payoneer.com"
					#HTTP::uri [string map {"/payer/" "/"} [HTTP::uri]]
					#log local0. "4. [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
					pool "QA2_ma_80"
					}
        "^/ma(/|$)" {
					HTTP::header replace "Host" "ma.qa2.payoneer.com"
					if {[HTTP::uri] contains "."} {
					HTTP::uri [string map {"/ma/" "/"} [HTTP::uri]]
					}
				    else {
				    HTTP::uri "/index.ma.html"
				    }
					pool "QA2_ma_80"
					log local0. "6. [LB::server addr] [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
					}
			default {
					pool "testmyaccount"
					#log local0. "5. [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
					}

	    }

}
}
ltm rule /Common/QA2_neo4j_bolt {
when HTTP_REQUEST {
  set active_server [active_nodes -list QA2_neo4jtrust-leader_7474]
  #log local0. "Current leader is: $active_server"

  node $active_server 7687
}
}
ltm rule /Common/QA2_new_direct_pools {
when CLIENT_ACCEPTED {
   set member_debug 0
   if { [IP::addr [IP::client_addr]/16 equals 192.168.0.0%[ROUTE::domain]] } {
      set office 1
      if {$member_debug} { log local0. "Client from office" }
   } elseif { [IP::addr [IP::client_addr]/24 equals 10.200.2.0%[ROUTE::domain]] } {
      set office 1
      if {$member_debug} { log local0. "Client from office" }
   } else {
      set office 0
      if {$member_debug} { log local0. "Client not from office" }
   }

}

when HTTP_REQUEST {
   # set office 1
   set member_lb [LB::server pool]
   if {$office} {

      # Log debug to /var/log/ltm? 1=yes, 0=no. Both should be set to 1
      set member_debug 0
      set webbo_logs 1

      # Set to 1 to active logs in webbo also and unremark
      #if { [HTTP::host] contains "webbo"} {  set webbo_logs 0 }

      # Name of the URI parameter name used to manually select a specific pool member
      # Clients can append the member parameter to a query string in the format of:
      #   www.example.com/index.html?member=2
      # where member is the parameter name
      set member_param "member"

      # Track whether a member has been found in the query string or cookie
      set member_num ""
      if { [HTTP::cookie member_lb] ne ""} {
         pool [HTTP::cookie member_lb]
         set member_lb [HTTP::cookie member_lb]
      }

      # Debug logging
      if { $member_debug and $webbo_logs} {
         log local0. "[LB::server pool]"
         log local0. "[IP::client_addr]:[TCP::client_port]: Debug enabled on [HTTP::method] request for [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
         log local0. "[IP::client_addr]:[TCP::client_port]: Members for pool [LB::server pool] (sorted):\
            [lsort [members -list [LB::server pool]]]"
      }

      # Check if query string contains "member=" before evaluating the value
      # Could replace this with a check of the URI that is only used when
      #   manually selecting a specific pool member.
      # Also check for a previously set cookie indicating a manually selected pool member.
      if {[HTTP::query] contains $member_param or [HTTP::cookie $member_param] ne ""} {
         # Have the query string parameter take precedence over the cookie.
         # So set the member_num based on the cookie and then overwrite it if the param value is set.
         set member_num [HTTP::cookie $member_param]
         if { $member_debug and $webbo_logs} { log local0. "[IP::client_addr]:[TCP::client_port]: Query contained the member parameter or member cookie was present.\
            Parsed member cookie value: $member_num" }

         set query_member_num [URI::query "?&[HTTP::query]" "&${member_param}"]
         if {$query_member_num ne ""} {
            set member_num $query_member_num
            if { $member_debug and $webbo_logs } { log local0. "[IP::client_addr]:[TCP::client_port]: Using member number from URI: \$member_num: $member_num" }
         }

         # Check member number value
         switch -glob $member_num {
            "0" {
               # Exact match for 0 (client wants to clear cookie)
               # Delete the cookie in the response

               # Save the cookie value so we can delete it in the response
               set cookie_val [HTTP::cookie $member_param]

               if {$member_debug and $webbo_logs} { log local0. "[IP::client_addr]:[TCP::client_port]: Member 0 specified, will remove cookie in response." }
               return
            }
            "[0-9]*" {
               # The parameter had a value starting with a digit,
               # Use lindex to get the nth -1 pool member "IP port" (lindex is 0 based)
               # Use scan to parse the IP and port to separate variables (the pool command doesn't seem to handle them together)
               # Use catch to handle any errors trying to parse the pool member
               if {[catch {scan [lindex [lsort [members -list [LB::server pool]]] [expr {$member_num - 1}]] {%[^ ] %d} ip port} result]} {

                  if { $member_debug and $webbo_logs } { log local0. "[IP::client_addr]:[TCP::client_port]: Error parsing pool member from $member_num" }

               } elseif {$result == 2} {

                  if { $member_debug and $webbo_logs } { log local0. "[IP::client_addr]:[TCP::client_port]: Parsed IP port: $ip $port" }

                  # Use catch to handle any errors trying to select the pool member
                  if {not [catch {node $ip $port}]} {
                     log local0. "URI is [HTTP::uri]"
                     log local0. "path is [HTTP::path]"
                     if {[URI::query [HTTP::uri]] contains $member_param} {
                        set newq ""
                        foreach param [split [URI::query [HTTP::uri]] "&"] {
                           if {!($param starts_with $member_param)} {
                              # Build up new query parameter string
                              if { $newq eq "" } {
                                 append newq "?$param"
                              } else {
                                 append newq "&$param"
                              }
                           }
                           # Add new query portion to path
                           HTTP::uri "[HTTP::path]$newq"
                        }
                     }
                     log local0. "URI is [HTTP::uri]"
                     log local0. "path is [HTTP::path]"
                     # Selecting pool member succeeded so exit this event of this iRule
                     if { $member_debug and $webbo_logs } { log local0. "[IP::client_addr]:[TCP::client_port]: Successfully selected: $ip $port" }
                     return
                  }
               }
            }
         }
         # If we're still in the iRule there was no match or there were errors trying to select the pool member
         # so load balance the request
         node [IP::client_addr]:[TCP::client_port]
         unset member_num --
         if { $member_debug and $webbo_logs } { log local0. "[IP::client_addr]:[TCP::client_port]: No/invalid member_num parsed, load balancing request" }
      }
   }
}

when HTTP_RESPONSE {

   # Check if $member_num is set and has a value
   if {[info exists member_num] and $member_num ne ""} {

      switch $member_num {
         0 {
            if {$cookie_val ne ""} {
               # Expire the cookie by inserting the name/value with an expire time in the past
               if { $member_debug and $webbo_logs } { log local0. "[IP::client_addr]:[TCP::client_port]: Expiring cookie $member_param=$cookie_val" }
               HTTP::cookie insert name $member_param value $cookie_val path "/"
               HTTP::cookie expires $member_param 0 absolute
               HTTP::cookie expires member_lb 0 absolute
            }
         }
         default {
            if { $member_debug and $webbo_logs} {log local0. "[IP::client_addr]:[TCP::client_port]: Inserting cookie $member_param=$member_num"}
            HTTP::cookie insert name $member_param value $member_num path "/"
            if {$member_debug and $webbo_logs} {log local0. "[IP::client_addr]:[TCP::client_port]: Inserting cookie member_lb=$member_lb"}
            HTTP::cookie insert name member_lb value $member_lb path "/"
         }
      }
   }
}
# Debug events which can be removed once testing is complete
when LB_SELECTED {
   if {$member_debug and $webbo_logs} { log local0. "[IP::client_addr]:[TCP::client_port]: Selected IP:port: [LB::server]" }
}
when SERVER_CONNECTED {
   if {$member_debug and $webbo_logs} { log local0. "[IP::client_addr]:[TCP::client_port]: Server IP:port: [IP::server_addr]:[TCP::server_port]" }
}
}
ltm rule /Common/QA2_nifi_rewrite {
when HTTP_REQUEST {
      log local0. "1. [HTTP::header Host]" 
	  if { [string tolower [HTTP::header Host]] contains "-nifi0" }{
	  HTTP::respond 302 Location "https://nifi.qa2.payoneer.com[HTTP::uri]"
	  } else {
	    eval [LB::select]
        set POOL [LB::server addr]
        #log local0. "Pool Member is $POOL"
        switch $POOL {
        172.16.0.94%1 { HTTP::header replace Host "il-nifi01-qa.qa2.payoneer.com" }
        172.16.0.95%1 { HTTP::header replace Host "il-nifi02-qa.qa2.payoneer.com" }
        172.16.0.96%1 { HTTP::header replace Host "il-nifi03-qa.qa2.payoneer.com" }
        } 
    }
}
}
ltm rule /Common/QA2_openapi_rewrite {
when HTTP_REQUEST {
  # Check for APIGEE auth header
  if { [string length [HTTP::header value Authorization]] <= 50 and [string length [HTTP::header value Authorization]] >= 10 and [HTTP::header value Authorization] starts_with "Bearer"} {
    HTTP::header insert "x-forwarded-host" [HTTP::host]
    HTTP::header replace "Host" "apiginternal.qa2.payoneer.com"
    virtual QA2_apigeegw_https
  }
  else {
    HTTP::header replace "Host" "api.qa2.payoneer.openapi.qa2.payoneer.com"
    pool QA2_openapi_443
  }
  #log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
}
}

			    }

ltm rule /Common/QA2_payoutsapi_new {
when CLIENT_ACCEPTED {
    set default_pool [LB::server pool]
}

when HTTP_REQUEST {
    set method [string tolower [HTTP::method]]
    switch -glob [string tolower [HTTP::uri]] {
        "/v2/*" {
            if { ( not [HTTP::header exists x-ratelimit-approved] ) && (([string tolower [HTTP::uri]] contains "/v2/programs/123123123/") || ([string tolower [HTTP::uri]] contains "/v2/programs/100056270/"))} {
                #log local0. "$method"
                HTTP::path [string map "/v2/ /payouts-api/proxy/$method/v2/" [HTTP::path] ]
                #log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
                #log local0. " #########     v2 YES UBER     ########"
                HTTP::header insert "x-forwarded-host" [HTTP::host]
                HTTP::header replace "Host" "apigopenapi.qa2.payoneer.com"
                virtual QA2_apigeegw_https
                #pool "QA2_datapower_443"
            } elseif { ([string tolower [HTTP::uri]] contains "/masspayouts") } {
                HTTP::header replace "Host" "masspayoutsingestor.qa2.payoneer.com"
                #log local0. "1[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
                #log local0. "2masspayouts redirect to pool: QA2_masspayoutsingestor_443"
                pool "QA2_masspayoutsingestor_443"
            } elseif { ([string tolower [HTTP::uri]] contains "/msmasspayouts") } {
                HTTP::header replace "Host" "masspayoutsingestor.qa2.payoneer.com"
                #log local0. "3[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
                #log local0. "4msmasspayouts redirect to pool: QA2_masspayoutsingestor_443"
                pool "QA2_masspayoutsingestor_443"
            } else {
                HTTP::path [string map {/v2/ /Payouts/HttpAPI/v2/} [HTTP::path] ]
                #HTTP::path "/Payouts/HttpAPI/v2/"
                #log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
                #log local0. "v2 not UBER"
                pool $default_pool
            }
        }
        "/v3/*" {
            HTTP::path [string map {/v3/ /Payouts/HttpAPI/v3/} [HTTP::path] ]
            #log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
            #log local0. " #########    v3    ########"
            pool $default_pool
        }
        "/v4/*" {
                HTTP::header insert "x-forwarded-host" [HTTP::host]
                HTTP::header replace "Host" "apigopenapi.qa2.payoneer.com"
                virtual QA2_apigeegw_https
                #pool "QA2_apigeegw_9097"
        }
        "/mrchtsrvcs/*" {
                #if { verify host header apicert }
                HTTP::header insert "x-forwarded-host" [HTTP::host]
                HTTP::header replace "Host" "apigmrchtsrvcs.qa2.payoneer.com"
                HTTP::uri [string map {"/mrchtsrvcs/" "/"} [HTTP::uri]]
                virtual QA2_apigeegw_https
        }
        "/integrations/*" {
                #if { verify host header apicert }
                HTTP::header insert "x-forwarded-host" [HTTP::host]
                HTTP::header replace "Host" "main-integrations.qa2.payoneer.com"
                HTTP::uri [string map {"/integrations/" "/"} [HTTP::uri]]
                virtual QA2_apigeegw_https
        }
        default {
            if { ( not [HTTP::header exists x-ratelimit-approved] ) && ([string tolower [HTTP::uri]] contains "/v2/programs/100056270/")} {
                #SSL::enable serverside
                #HTTP::path [string map "/Payouts/HttpAPI/v2/ /payoneer/qa-internal/proxy/$method/Payouts/HttpAPI/v2/" [HTTP::path] ]
                #pool "QA2_datapower_443"

                HTTP::path [string map "/Payouts/HttpAPI/v2/ /payouts-api/proxy/$method/v2/" [HTTP::path] ]
                #log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
                #log local0. " #########     v2 YES UBER     ########"
                HTTP::header insert "x-forwarded-host" [HTTP::host]
                HTTP::header replace "Host" "apigopenapi.qa2.payoneer.com"
                virtual QA2_apigeegw_https
            } elseif { [string tolower [HTTP::uri]] contains "/payouts/httpapi/api.aspx?mname=performpayoutpayment&p1=" } {
                            #log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
                            #log local0. "Default Round Robin F5 pool"
                            #log local0. "redirect to pool: QA2_api_ppp_genpop_443"
                            pool $default_pool
            } elseif { [string tolower [HTTP::uri]] contains "payouts/httpapi" } {
                            #log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
                            #log local0. "Default Round Robin F5 pool"
                            #log local0. "redirect to pool: QA2_apipayouts_80"
                            pool $default_pool
           } else {
                #log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
                #log local0. "hereeeeeee"
                pool $default_pool
            }
        }
    }
}
}

when CLIENT_ACCEPTED {

}

when HTTP_REQUEST {
    set method [string tolower [HTTP::method]]
    switch -glob [string tolower [HTTP::uri]] {

                #log local0. "$method"
                HTTP::path [string map "/v2/ /payouts-api/proxy/$method/v2/" [HTTP::path] ]
                #log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
                #log local0. " #########     v2 YES UBER     ########"

                HTTP::header replace "Host" "apigopenapi.qa2.payoneer.com"
                virtual QA2_apigeegw_https
                #pool "QA2_datapower_443"
            } elseif {[string match {/v2/programs/*/masspayouts} [string tolower [HTTP::uri]]]} {

                #log local0. "Check for Ebay"
                HTTP::path [string map {/v2/ /Payouts/HttpAPI/v2/} [HTTP::path] ]
                #log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
                log local0. "Ebay redirect to pool: QA2_api_ing_443"
                pool $default_pool
            } else {
                HTTP::path [string map {/v2/ /Payouts/HttpAPI/v2/} [HTTP::path] ]
                #HTTP::path "/Payouts/HttpAPI/v2/"
                #log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
                #log local0. "v2 not UBER"
                pool $default_pool
            }
        }
        "/v3/*" {
            HTTP::path [string map {/v3/ /Payouts/HttpAPI/v3/} [HTTP::path] ]
            #log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
            #log local0. " #########    v3    ########"
            pool $default_pool
        }
        "/v4/*" {
              # Check for APIGEE auth header
              if { [string length [HTTP::header value Authorization]] <= 50 and [string length [HTTP::header value Authorization]] >= 10 } {
                HTTP::header insert "x-forwarded-host" [HTTP::host]
                HTTP::header replace "Host" "apigopenapi.qa2.payoneer.com"
                virtual QA2_apigeegw_https
                #pool "QA2_apigeegw_9097"
              # Default - send to IBM
              } else {
                HTTP::uri "/payoneer/qa[HTTP::uri]"
                #log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
                #log local0. " #########    v4    ########"
                pool "QA2_datapower_443"
              }
        }
        default {
            if { ( not [HTTP::header exists x-ratelimit-approved] ) && ([string tolower [HTTP::uri]] contains "/v2/programs/100056270")} {
                #SSL::enable serverside
                HTTP::path [string map "/Payouts/HttpAPI/v2/ /payoneer/qa-internal/proxy/$method/Payouts/HttpAPI/v2/" [HTTP::path] ]
                pool "QA2_datapower_443"
            } elseif { [string tolower [HTTP::uri]] contains "/payouts/httpapi/api.aspx?mname=performpayoutpayment&p1=" } {
                            #log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
                            #log local0. "Default Round Robin F5 pool"
                            log local0. "redirect to pool: QA2_api_ppp_genpop_443"
                            pool $default_pool
            } elseif { [string tolower [HTTP::uri]] contains "payouts/httpapi" } {
                            #log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
                            #log local0. "Default Round Robin F5 pool"
                            log local0. "redirect to pool: QA2_apipayouts_80"
                            pool $default_pool
           } else {
                #log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
                #log local0. "hereeeeeee"
                pool $default_pool
            }
        }
    }
}

when HTTP_RESPONSE {
    if { [HTTP::status] contains "404"} {
        HTTP::redirect https://www.payoneer.com/404/
    }
}
}
ltm rule /Common/QA2_payoutsapi_v2 {
when CLIENT_ACCEPTED {

}

    set method [string tolower [HTTP::method]]

                log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
                #log local0. "$method"
                HTTP::path [string map "/v2/ /payouts-api/proxy/$method/v2/" [HTTP::path] ]
                #log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
                #log local0. " #########     v2 YES UBER     ########"
                HTTP::header insert "x-forwarded-host" [HTTP::host]
                HTTP::header replace "Host" "apigopenapi.qa2.payoneer.com"

                #pool "QA2_apigeegw_9097"
            } else {

                #HTTP::path "/Payouts/HttpAPI/v2/"
                log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
                #log local0. "v2 not UBER"

            }
        }
        "/v3/*" {
            HTTP::path [string map {/v3/ /Payouts/HttpAPI/v3/} [HTTP::path] ]
            #log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
            #log local0. " #########    v3    ########"
            pool $default_pool
        }
        "/v4/*" {
              # Check for APIGEE auth header
              if { [string length [HTTP::header value Authorization]] <= 50 and [string length [HTTP::header value Authorization]] >= 10 } {
                HTTP::header insert "x-forwarded-host" [HTTP::host]
                HTTP::header replace "Host" "apigopenapi.qa2.payoneer.com"
                virtual QA2_apigeegw_https
                #pool "QA2_apigeegw_9097"
              # Default - send to IBM
              } else {
                HTTP::uri "/payoneer/qa[HTTP::uri]"
                #log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
                #log local0. " #########    v4    ########"
                pool "QA2_datapower_443"
              }
        }
        default {
            if { ( not [HTTP::header exists x-ratelimit-approved] ) && ([string tolower [HTTP::uri]] contains "/v2/programs/100056270")} {
                #SSL::enable serverside
                HTTP::path [string map "/Payouts/HttpAPI/v2/ /payouts-api/proxy/$method/Payouts/HttpAPI/v2/" [HTTP::path] ]
                HTTP::header insert "x-forwarded-host" [HTTP::host]
                HTTP::header replace "Host" "apigopenapi.qa2.payoneer.com"
                virtual QA2_apigeegw_https
                #pool "QA2_datapower_443"
            } else {
                #log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
                #log local0. "hereeeeeee"
                pool $default_pool
            }
        }
    }
}

ltm rule /Common/QA2_payoutsapi_v2_v3_only {
when HTTP_REQUEST { 
    if { [HTTP::uri] starts_with "/v2/" } { 
        HTTP::path [string map {/v2/ /Payouts/HttpAPI/v2/} [string tolower [HTTP::path]] ]
         #HTTP::path "/Payouts/HttpAPI/v2/" 
        #log local0. "===== redirectiong /v2/ url to new one"
    }
    if { [HTTP::uri] starts_with "/v3/" } { 
        HTTP::path [string map {/v3/ /Payouts/HttpAPI/v3/} [string tolower [HTTP::path]] ]
    }
}
}
ltm rule /Common/QA2_psd2_gw-rewrite {
when CLIENTSSL_HANDSHAKE {

  set cur [SSL::sessionid]
  set ask [session lookup ssl $cur]
  if { $ask eq "" } {
    session add ssl [SSL::sessionid] [SSL::cert 0]
  }
}

when HTTP_REQUEST {

  set id [SSL::sessionid]
  set the_cert [session lookup ssl $id]
  if { $the_cert != ""} {

    HTTP::header replace "X-Client-Certificate" [b64encode $the_cert]
  }

  # Check for apigee token
  if { [string length [HTTP::header value Authorization]] <= 50 and [string length [HTTP::header value Authorization]] >= 10 } {
    HTTP::header insert "x-forwarded-host" [HTTP::host]
    HTTP::header replace "Host" "apigpsd2.qa2.payoneer.com"
    HTTP::uri "/psd2[HTTP::uri]"
    virtual QA2_apigeegw_https
  # Default - send to IBM
  } else {
    HTTP::uri "/payoneer/qa-psd2[HTTP::uri]"
  }
}
}
ltm rule /Common/QA2_pubs_rewrites {
when HTTP_REQUEST { 
    set rewrite_trigger [string tolower [HTTP::uri]]
    #log local0. "0. [LB::server addr] [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
	    switch -regexp $rewrite_trigger {
	             "^/ma-docker/" {
					set uri2 [string range [HTTP::uri] 10 end]
					HTTP::uri $uri2
					pool "ma-docker-test"
					#log local0. "1. [LB::server addr] [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
					}
	             "^/ma-myaccountmock/" {
					HTTP::header replace "Host" "ma-myaccountmock.qa2.payoneer.com"
					set uri2 [string range [HTTP::uri] 17 end]
					HTTP::uri $uri2
					pool "QA2_myaccountmock_80"
					#log local0. "1. [LB::server addr] [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
					}
	    		 "^/ma/" {
					HTTP::header replace "Host" "ma.qa2.payoneer.com"
					set uri2 [string range [HTTP::uri] 3 end]
					HTTP::uri $uri2
					pool "QA2_ma_80"
					#log local0. "1. [LB::server addr] [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
					}

					"^/ma-" {
					set uri1 [HTTP::uri]
					set maid [substr $uri1 1 "/"]
                    HTTP::header replace "Host" $maid.qa2.payoneer.com
				    HTTP::uri [string map -nocase "/$maid/ /" [HTTP::uri]]
				    pool "QA2_mafeaturerelease_80"
				    #log local0. "[LB::server]" 
				    #log local0. "4. [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
					}

					"^/login/" {
					HTTP::header replace "Host" "login.qa2.payoneer.com"
					set uri2 [string range [HTTP::uri] 6 end]
					HTTP::uri $uri2
					pool "QA2_login_80"
					#log local0. "1. [LB::server addr] [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
					}

					"^/login-" {
					set uri1 [HTTP::uri]
					set loginid [substr $uri1 1 "/"]
                    HTTP::header replace "Host" $loginid.qa2.payoneer.com
				    HTTP::uri [string map -nocase "/$loginid/ /" [HTTP::uri]]
				    pool "QA2_mafeaturerelease_80"
				    #log local0. "[LB::server]" 
				    #log local0. "4. [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
					}

					"^/auth/" {
					HTTP::header replace "Host" "auth.qa2.payoneer.com"
					set uri2 [string range [HTTP::uri] 5 end]
					HTTP::uri $uri2
					pool "QA2_auth_80"
					#log local0. "1. [LB::server addr] [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
					}

			default {
					pool "QA2_pubs_80"
#					log local0. "3. [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
					}

	    }

}
}
ltm rule /Common/QA2_riskapps_rewrite {
when HTTP_REQUEST {
  switch [string tolower [HTTP::host]] {

      pool "QA2_riskapps_8050"
    }

      pool "QA2_riskapps_8060"
    }

    }

      #log local0. "routed to port 9020"
      pool "QA2_riskapps_9020"
    }

    }

    default {

        </head>

        The service you request for is not available<br>
        </body>
        </html>
      }
    }

  }

}

ltm rule /Common/QA2_signupapi_rewrite {
when HTTP_REQUEST {
    if { [HTTP::uri] starts_with "/api" }{
        HTTP::header replace "Host" "signupapi.QA2.payoneer.com"
                    #log local0. "3. [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
                    pool "QA2_signupapi_80"
                    }
    else {
        pool "QA2_signup_80"
        }
}
}
ltm rule /Common/QA2_webbo_newrewrites {
when HTTP_REQUEST {

set hostname [string tolower [HTTP::host]]
set uri [string tolower [HTTP::uri]]

if { [class match $uri starts_with QA2_webbo_dg] } {

    set parameters_DG [class match -value $uri starts_with QA2_webbo_dg]
    set NEW_HOST [getfield $parameters_DG # 1 ]
    set SLIT_POINT [getfield $parameters_DG # 2 ]
    set TO_POOL [getfield $parameters_DG # 3 ]

               HTTP::header replace "Host" $NEW_HOST
               set uri2 [string range [HTTP::uri] $SLIT_POINT end]
               HTTP::uri $uri2
    pool $TO_POOL
log local0. "3. [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"               
               }
else {
					pool "QA2_webbo_80"
					#log local0. "3. [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
					}

}
}

ltm rule /Common/QA2_webbogw_rewrite {
when CLIENT_ACCEPTED {
    log local0. "appian tcp started"
}
when HTTP_REQUEST {
    log local0. "[HTTP::host]"
    log local0. "case started"
    if {[HTTP::host] eq "webbogw.qa2.payoneer.com" } {
        log local0. "correct host header "
        HTTP::header insert "x-forwarded-host" [HTTP::host]
        HTTP::header replace "Host" "apigwebbo.qa2.payoneer.com"
        log local0. "[HTTP::uri]"
        #HTTP::uri "/gw-merchant[HTTP::uri]"
        log local0. "[HTTP::uri]"
        log local0. "good"
        pool QA2_apigeegw_9103 
    } else {
        HTTP::respond 302 Location "https://www.payoneer.com/oops/"
        log local0. "302"
    }
}
}
ltm rule /Common/QA2_wiremock_http {
when HTTP_REQUEST { 
    if { [IP::addr [IP::client_addr] equals 10.30.20.0%[ROUTE::domain]/24] }{ 
       #log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri] Allowed HTTP internally for subnet 20" }
    elseif { [IP::addr [IP::client_addr] equals 10.30.21.0%[ROUTE::domain]/24] }{ 
       #log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri] Allowed HTTP internally for subnet 21" }
       elseif { [IP::addr [IP::client_addr] equals 172.16.0.0%[ROUTE::domain]/24] }{ 
       #log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri] Allowed HTTP internally for subnet 16" }
       elseif {[string tolower [HTTP::uri]] contains "swagger"}{
       #SSL::disable clientside
       log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri] uri contains swagger" }
       else {
		HTTP::redirect https://[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]
		#log local0. "[IP::client_addr] ========================"
		#log local0. "[HTTP::host][HTTP::uri] redirect to HTTPS" 
    }
}
}
ltm rule /Common/QA2_wiremock_ssl_disable {
when CLIENT_ACCEPTED {
    #http requests range
    SSL::disable
        #https requests range
        if {([TCP::local_port] >= 15000 && [TCP::local_port] <= 20000 ) }{
            SSL::enable
            SSL::profile payoneer_qa_ssl
            }
}
}
ltm rule /Common/debug {
when HTTP_REQUEST {
    log local0. "kube virt reached"
}
}
ltm rule /Common/direct_nodes {
when CLIENT_ACCEPTED {
    set member_debug 0
    if { [IP::addr [IP::client_addr]/16 equals 192.168.0.0%[ROUTE::domain]] }{
       set office 1
       if {$member_debug}{log local0. "Client from office"}
    } else {
       set office 0
       if {$member_debug}{log local0. "Client not from office"}}}
}
ltm rule /Common/direct_pools {
when HTTP_REQUEST {
     set host [string tolower [HTTP::host]]
     set subd ""
     set uri ""
     scan $host {%[^.]%s} subd uri
     #log local0. "subdomain = $subd
     if {$subd matches_regex {[0-9]}} {
        set spool "QA2_${subd}_80"
        #log local0. "redirect to internal pool: $spool"
        pool $spool
     }
}
}
ltm rule /Common/print_headers {
when HTTP_REQUEST {

    if {[HTTP::uri] equals "/externalapi/v1/ExternalExecuteSupportLog"} {
        log local0. "=================START Request=================="
        set LogString "Client [IP::client_addr]:[TCP::client_port] -> [HTTP::host][HTTP::uri]"
        log local0. "$LogString (request)"
        log local0. "[HTTP::header count]"
        #foreach aHeader [HTTP::header names] {
         #log local0. "$aHeader: [HTTP::header values $aHeader]"
        #}
        #log local0. "Selected pool member [TCP::server_port] Client [IP::client_addr]"

        # llength uses the spaces as well as carriage returns and line feeds
        log local0. "list length: [llength [HTTP::request]], all headers: [HTTP::request]"

        # Log the request headers in hex
        binary scan [HTTP::request] H* request_hex
        log local0. "hex: $request_hex"

        # Replace the main whitespace characters with their hex equivalent (ie, " " -> \x20)
        log local0. "escaped: [string map {\x20 \\x20 \x0d \\x0d \x0a \\x0a} [HTTP::request]]"

        # Use string map to remove the \x0d carriage return
        #    then split the string on the \x0a linefeeds into a list
        set headers [split [string map {\x0d ""} [HTTP::request]] \x0a]
        set len [llength $headers]

        # Loop through each request header line and log it
        for { set i 0 } { $i <  $len+1 } { incr i } {
            log local0. "$i = [lindex $headers $i]"
        }

       log local0. "=================END Request====================="
    }
}
}
ltm rule /Common/testy {
when HTTP_REJECT {
    log local0. "THIS is good"
}
}

ltm profile server-ssl /Common/payoneer_server_ssl {
    alert-timeout indefinite
    allow-expired-crl disabled
    app-service none
    authenticate once
    authenticate-depth 9
    authenticate-name none
    ca-file none
    cache-size 262144
    cache-timeout 3600
    cert none
    chain none
    cipher-group none
    ciphers DEFAULT
    crl-file none
    data-0rtt disabled
    defaults-from /Common/serverssl
    generic-alert enabled
    handshake-timeout 10
    key none
    max-active-handshakes indefinite
    mod-ssl-methods disabled
    mode enabled
    options { dont-insert-empty-fragments no-tlsv1.3 no-dtlsv1.2 }
    peer-cert-mode ignore
    proxy-ssl disabled
    proxy-ssl-passthrough disabled
    renegotiate-period indefinite
    renegotiate-size indefinite
    renegotiation enabled
    retain-certificate true
    revoked-cert-status-response-control drop
    secure-renegotiation require-strict
    server-name none
    session-mirroring disabled
    session-ticket disabled
    sni-default false
    sni-require false
    ssl-forward-proxy disabled
    ssl-forward-proxy-bypass disabled
    ssl-sign-hash any
    strict-resume disabled
    unclean-shutdown enabled
    unknown-cert-status-response-control ignore
}

ltm profile tcp /Common/default-tcp-wan {
    abc enabled
    app-service none
    auto-proxy-buffer-size enabled
    auto-receive-window-size enabled
    auto-send-buffer-size enabled
    cmetrics-cache enabled
    cmetrics-cache-timeout 0
    congestion-control bbr
    defaults-from /Common/f5-tcp-wan
    delay-window-control disabled
    ecn enabled
    init-cwnd 10
    pkt-loss-ignore-burst 0
    pkt-loss-ignore-rate 0
    proxy-buffer-high 262144
    proxy-buffer-low 196608
    rate-pace disabled
    rate-pace-max-rate 0
    receive-window-size 131072
    send-buffer-size 262144
    slow-start enabled
    timestamps enabled
}

    forward-zones {
        amazonaws.com {
            nameservers {
                8.8.8.8:53 { }
            }
        }
        idservice.net {
            nameservers {
                8.8.8.8:53 { }
            }
        }
        shpapi.com {
            nameservers {
                8.8.8.8:53 { }
            }
        }
    }
    route-domain /Common/0
}

    network default%1
